sentences: Jude (born Michael Jude Christodal, October 16, 1969, Boston, Massachusetts) is an American singer and songwriter.
Jude's debut album, 430 N. Harper Ave, was released independently by the Fish of Death label in 1997.
His follow-up album, King of Yesterday was released on September 11, 2001.
Jude soon parted ways with Maverick and produced his subsequent albums independently (Sarah in 2004 and Redemption in 2006).
Jude soon parted ways with Maverick and produced his subsequent albums independently (Sarah in 2004 and Redemption in 2006).
Naive released Redemption in Europe in September 2006, and released the single "Save Me" via iTunes in October.
The whole album was released in the US in November 2006.
In 2006, Jude, Chris Seefried, Jeff Russo and Dave Gibbs formed the band Low Stars.
They released an eponymous CD through the Starbucks Hear music label in 2007.
In August 2007, Jude left the Low Stars.
In 2015, he launched a PledgeMusic campaign to record the EP Me and My Monster, which was released in 2016.

His follow-up album, King of Yesterday was released on September 11, 2001.
Currently, Jude is signed with Naive records in Paris, France.
Naive released Redemption in Europe in September 2006, and released the single "Save Me" via iTunes in October.
Jude is currently based in Los Angeles, writing songs for film and television.
"Love, Love, Love" was featured in a 2007 episode of the television drama, What About Brian; "Stay" was featured in the last scene of the final episode of that series.
"Out of LA" was featured in a 2005 episode of the series.
